column2: Funko, Inc. is a pop culture consumer products company. The company is headquartered in Everett, Washington and currently employs 921 full-time employees. The firm is engaged in selling a broad range of pop culture consumer products, featuring characters from a range of media and entertainment content, including movies, TV shows, video games, music and sports. Its products combine its proprietary brands and designs into properties it licenses from content providers. Its product categories include figures, plush, accessories and other. The company also offers different types of bags and wallets. The company offers its products under various brands, including Pop!, Mystery Minis, Dorbz, Pint Size Heroes, Rock Candy, Galactic or Hero Plushies, SuperCute, MyMoji and Loungefly. The firm has licensed properties into four categories: classic evergreen, movie release, current TV and current video game.
